{"id": "1398340165482844302", "channel_id": "1398340165482844302", "type": 0, "author_id": "272394963642220545", "author_name": "__goz__", "author_bot": false, "content": "Please clarify once and for all the odds of getting a limited character from the standard banner (& same for wheels).\n\nIs the \"*0.5% SSR Awakener overall drop rate*\" in reference :\n- to a 0.5% chance to hit a standard limited on every pull (implying the chance for an SSR non-limited is `3.03-0.5 = 2.53%` per pull)\n- to a 0.5% *comprehensive drop rate*(in relation with the ***5.00%***¹ overall SSR drop rate including pity), meaning you run a 1/10 chance roll for standard limited on every successful SSR hit\n- to a 0.5% chance of an SSR being a standard limited, meaning a 1/200 roll for limited on every successful SSR hit\n\nAlso, I tagged this as **Game Suggestion** since I would love it if the answer could replace the current in-game description for maximum clarity.\n\nThanks in advance !\n\n\n¹ : *calculations suggests the drop rate of SSR for p=0.0303 & pity of 30 over an infinite number of pulls to be ~5.027% and not 5.00% (see [there](https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/1850986/how-does-a-pity-timer-affects-probabilities))*", "timestamp": "2025-07-25T16:24:35.355000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-07-26T00:06:58.834000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [{"id": "1398340166522765485", "filename": "Screenshot_2025-07-25_18-13-51.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 508916, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1398340165482844302/1398340166522765485/Screenshot_2025-07-25_18-13-51.png?ex=6a00b143&is=69ff5fc3&hm=d84ccc1812d01356ab0873722139b18b84269ebf6bd39519d5a1fda0c24d7428&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1398340165482844302", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Clarification on gacha odds for standard limited", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276